          "6.46  Tapasvibhyah  etc.  The superiority  [of  Yogin]  over the men of austerities has already been indicated.  The knowledge is the fruit of Yoga.  Hence Yogin's  superiority over the men of  knowledge. He is superior to men of action, because he alone knows how to perform action.\t\n The God-discarding difficult Yoga, does not itself yield success. This is stated [as]-",
      "sc":
          "।।6.46।।योगस्य प्राधान्यमाह  तपस्विभ्य इति।  तपस्विभ्यः अधिकत्वं पूर्वमेव सूचितम्।  ज्ञानिभ्यः अधिकत्वं ज्ञानस्य योगफलत्वात्।  कर्मिभ्य उत्कर्षः स एव कर्माणि कर्तुं वेत्ति।"
    },
