    "abhinav": {
      "author": "Sri Abhinav Gupta",
      "et":
          "6.9 Suhrt etc.  Friend is one whose heart remains good  and auspicious without cause  (on its own accord).  Companionship is  [that which is felt] mutually.  Enmity is  [also that which is felt] between one another.  The indifferent one :  the one, who is free from both these.  One who remains in the middle :  he who is partly a friend and  partly an enemy. Foe : he who deserves to be hated,  [but] cannot be hated.  Relative : the one [connected] by marital  bondage.  Whosoever is with his mind eal to all these as well as  to the righteous and the sinful; he excells  [all]  i.e.,  stage after stage he goes out of the cycle of birth-and-death.\t\t\n By the worshipful-footed persons of this sort -",
      "sc":
          "।।6.9।।सुहृदिति।  सुहृत् यस्य हृदयम् अकारणमेव शोभनम्।  मित्रत्वम् अन्योन्यम्।  अरित्वं परस्परम्।  उदासीन एतदुभयरहितः (S N K (n) एतद्रूपरहितः)  मध्यस्थः केनचिदंशेन मित्रं केनचिच्छत्रुः।  द्वेषार्हो द्वेष्टुमशक्यो (N द्वेष्टुं शक्यः) द्वेष्यः।  बन्धुः योन्यादिसंबन्धेन।  एतेषु सर्वेषु समधीः एवं साधुषु पापेषु च स च विशिष्यते क्रमात् क्रम संसारात् तरति।"
